cells.name: Usage
cells.note:
Heartbeat counts per subsystem
==============================

This dashboard shows hearbeats as replicated from systems running at the Summit. It also shows connector alerts, which help us to correlate connector failures with missing data.

You should expect to see heartbeats in nearly realtime here.

Interruption in the heartbeats tells us that: 

- The subsystem stopped running at the Summit. To confirm that check the same dashboard at the Summit, or look for alerts at #com-efd-status. In this case you should see alerts for the Summit EFD and USDF EFD for the same subsystem.

- Or the replication from Summit to USDF is not working. To confirm that you can check Kafdrop to see if messages are arrinving in Kafka. Looking up at any heartbeat topic should be enough because replication is done through a single connector. 

- Or there's a problem with the InfluxDB connectors at USDF. Data is arriving to the Kafka but is not recorded in the InfluxDB instance at USDF.

By default heartbeats counts are aggregated in intervals set by the dashaboard ``:interval:`` variable. The value in the y-axis is not important, they change depending on the aggregation window.

It is a good idea to use annotations to describe events associated with missing heartbeats, specially those not related to a connector failure, e.g. loosing connection to the calibration hill.
